description:
&lt;p&gt;Southwark Operations Directorate have commissioned a 12 month pilot for a psychologically informed Crisis Service at the Maudsley Hospital. The service has been provisionally named the Southwark ‘Safe Space’ and is an exciting and innovative addition to existing Crisis provision in Southwark.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Safe Space Crisis Service will offer a supportive, therapeutic space and psychologically focussed crisis interventions to people presenting in mental health crisis within the borough. The Safe Space will be situated on the Maudsley hospital site and will be open from 17:00 to midnight seven days a week; the post holder will work a shift pattern in line with the operational hours, which may be subject to change during the pilot. The post holder may be required to work across different Trust sites according to the needs of the borough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Peer Support Worker within the Safe Space Crisis Service. We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic compassionate, positive thinking and self-motivated individual that has lived experience of mental health problems and recovery, preferably with experience of using crisis services in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role has been specifically designed for people with lived experience of mental health difficulties and using mental health services. You will use your experiences and skills to provide support to service users using our Safe Space Crisis Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peer Support Workers will work alongside service users to work towards their recovery, supporting in reducing people’s mental health crisis and promoting independence. The post holder will use their lived experience to promote hope that recovery is possible. The post holder must have personal lived experience of recovery from mental health challenges, having used mental health services. We are looking for people who are willing to positively share their personal experiences with others in order to support service users in their journey of recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based within the Safe Space Crisis Service, the post holder will be a member of a multidisciplinary team working alongside mental health professionals. Peer Support Workers will carry out a variety of duties, such as welcoming service users into the Safe Space, supporting them with personal recovery goals, assisting with groups and offering 1 to1 time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder need to be a motivated, organised, energetic and a flexible team worker with effective communication and interpersonal skills in order to liaise with patients, carers and professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peer Support Workers will be fully supported in their role through regular 1 to 1 supervision within the team line management structure. You will also have access to training opportunities to support your professional development, including an accredited Peer Worker training course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Safe Space Crisis Service will be based in Maudsley Hospital, Denmark Hill, London, SE5 8AZ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust headquarters is located at Denmark Hill less than 5 minutes from the train station (zone 2). We also provide services and operate across other locations, such as London boroughs of Croydon, Lambeth, Lewisham and Southwark; and substance misuse services for residents of Bexley, Lambeth, Greenwich and Wandsworth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to ensuring our staff get the most out of their benefits package and understand the importance of a healthy work life balance. There is an extensive range of excellent benefits for you and your family. We want you to feel like you are part of a close knit team at SLaM. It’s important to us that you valued and appreciated and that are why we have a comprehensive benefits package on offer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of our benefits are highlighted here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generous pay, pensions and leave, &lt;/strong&gt;we offer a comprehensive pay, pensions and leave package which is dependent on the role and length of service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work life balance, &lt;/strong&gt;flexible working and support a range of flexible options, such as: part-time working and job sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career development, &lt;/strong&gt;There are plenty of opportunities to progress your career and we support your development through a number of programmes such as mentoring, coaching, positive people management, collective leadership and other talent programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car lease, &lt;/strong&gt;our staff benefits from competitive deals to lease cars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accommodation, &lt;/strong&gt;our staff benefits from keyworker housing available which is available on selected sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS discounts, &lt;/strong&gt;with discounts up to 10% from a variety of well-known retail brands though Health Service Discounts website.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other benefits include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Counselling services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long service awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season ticket loan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff restaurants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
